data.name: lbl7.ToolTip
data.value:
The Service must define two contracts, one for Request and one for Response Only those two are allowed per MicroService The MicroService inherits IntegrationServiceBase<<ProductName>ServiceRequest,<ProductName>ServiceResponse>
The Facade or the Unit Test Must create a caller Context supplying CompanyId, LoanId, then Create The request Object with this CallerContext The caller should also Provide a productType, there should be an FQN class saved to the product In Vendor Manager Then Call the <ProductName>Service.GetServiceResponse GetServiceResponse will call the base class in this order GetServiceContext(request, response); OnBeforeStartProcessing(context) OnStartProcessing(context); OnCompleteProcessing(context); DoValidation ProcessIntegration
You should write code in GetServiceContext to Get ProviderHelper pass, ProductType This will get the venor manager settings Then do any validations required in DoValidation Then write the actual service code in ProcessIntegration
All MicroServices must copy TheServiceHost.exe and reference it. This becomes the ServiceHost for this service. It will read the Configuration and Host the Service DLL for Example take TheServiceHost.exe and rename it to <ProductName>Service.exe Then rename TheServiceHost.exe.config to <ProductName>Service.exe and change its contents to Match your service then run this exe to host the service so you can generate the proxy

data.name: dfsResponse.Text
data.value: The box above should start with GET or POST which is the http verb used for the test. Then the URL followed by the body parameters for post or the Url parameters for Get. Clicking Send on Empty box will generate the test parameters
